-- E8 (#3 census-B runtime header-dispatch fallback for `++`): a string-builder
-- helper whose `++` operand static LTy the emitter CANNOT recover.  `acc` has no
-- type-forcing use before the `++`, so two-pass signature inference leaves it the
-- LTInt default; the `++` therefore can't statically pick string-vs-list append
-- (E2a/E7 don't apply) and falls to the E8 runtime fallback — `@mdk_append`,
-- which inspects the left cell header and routes to string vs list append.
-- This mirrors the scanTriple/splitLines string-builder shape that left ~333
-- `++` sites in the #3 gap.  The accumulator is actually a String at runtime;
-- the result is projected through `stringLength` (a type-forcing String read) so
-- it is consumed correctly and byte-identically regardless of the fallback's
-- statically-defaulted result LTy.  Oracle: 6 (= length of "foobar").
build acc s = acc ++ s

main = stringLength (build "foo" "bar")
